# Confidence Engine — Implementation Plan

Build **Layer 12 — Confidence & Self-Validation Engine** per §2.12. This engine computes a global confidence score using a weighted mean formula and triggers specific system actions (deliver, warn, expand, or clarify) based on strict thresholds.

## Proposed Changes

### Schemas

#### [NEW] [schemas.py](file:///c:/HelioX/confidence/schemas.py)

| Model | Purpose |
|-------|---------|
| `ConfidenceAction` (Enum) | Maps to decision thresholds: `DELIVER`, `DELIVER_WITH_WARNING`, `EXPAND_RETRIEVAL`, `REQUEST_CLARIFICATION`. |
| `ConfidenceWeights` | The expected calibration vectors: [coverage](file:///c:/HelioX/retrieval/dynamic_k.py#24-52) (0.20), [citation_density](file:///c:/HelioX/tests/test_adjudication.py#214-221) (0.20), `worker_agreement` (0.20), `conflict_severity` (0.15), [authority_score](file:///c:/HelioX/adjudication/authority.py#39-107) (0.15), `avg_cosine_similarity` (0.10). |
| `ConfidenceEvaluation` | Output schema: `global_confidence`, `action`, `sub_scores` (dictionary for debugging), `is_calibrated` flag. |

